Allison Glock was born in West Virginia[1] and is an American non-fiction writer.[2] She graduated from Indiana University, and from Syracuse University with an MA. Her work has appeared in The New York Times,[3] The New York Times Magazine, Esquire,[4] GQ, , Maxim,[5] Men's Journal, The New Yorker, Food & Wine, Elle, Garden & Gun, Oprah Magazine, Marie Claire, Rolling Stone. She is a Senior Staff Writer for ESPN.[6]
